<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1436,638,1155]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,986,1011]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is currently endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[706,766,986,1011]" name="Chile" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Chile</collectingCountry>
and belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[999,1109,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">persimilis</emphasis>
subgroup (with smooth egg shell) within the 
<taxonomicName box="[391,497,1022,1047]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Macrobiotidae" genus="Macrobiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="hufelandi">
<emphasis box="[391,497,1022,1047]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">hufelandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. This group requires careful taxonomic analysis, including egg morphology, to differentiate the individual species (
<bibRefCitation author="Bertolani" box="[627,938,1058,1083]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Bertolani, R. &amp; Rebecchi, L. (1993) A revision of the Macrobiotus hufelandi group (Tardigrada, Macrobiotidae), with some observations on the taxonomic characters of eutardigrades. Zoologica Scripta, 22, 127 - 152. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1993. tb 00347. x" type="journal article" year="1993">
Bertolani &amp; Rebecchi 
<number box="[879,938,1059,1083]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; new species within this group: e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pilato" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Pilato, G., Kaczmarek, L., Michalczyk, L. &amp; Lisi, O. (2003 b) Macrobiotus polonicus, a new species of Tardigrada from Poland (Eutardigrada, Macrobiotidae, ' hufelandi group'). Zootaxa, 258, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="b">
Pilato 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[234,292,1094,1119]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" value="2003.0">2003</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
, Kaczmarek &amp; Michalczyk 
<number box="[618,677,1095,1119]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" value="2004.0">2004</number>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fontoura" box="[687,915,1094,1119]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Fontoura, P., Pilato, G. &amp; Lisi, O. (2008) New records of eutardigrades (Tardigrada) from Faial and Pico Islands, the Azores, with the description of two new species. Zootaxa, 1778, 37 - 47." type="journal article" year="2008">
Fontoura 
<emphasis box="[794,850,1094,1119]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[856,915,1095,1119]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartels" box="[925,1131,1094,1119]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Bartels, P., Pilato, G., Lisi, O. &amp; Nelson, D. R. (2009) Macrobiotus (Eutardigrada, Macrobiotidae) from the Great Smoky Mountains National Park, Tennessee / North Carolina, USA (North America): two new species and six new records. Zootaxa, 2022, 45 - 57." type="journal article" year="2009">
